# Info
Invoked when the server starts. This is the main event for running code when the server (or singleplayer world) has finished loading.

# Available Event Fields
- `event.server` - the Minecraft server instance

# Example

```js
ServerEvents.loaded(event => {
	console.log('Server has loaded!')
})
```

```js
ServerEvents.loaded(event => {
	// Send a welcome message to all online players (useful for dedicated servers)
	event.server.tell('Server scripts have been reloaded!')
})
```
